928
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:46,200
 His first half of life descended from heaven.

929
00:40:46,200 --> 00:40:48,920
 His second half of life ascended from heaven.

930
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:53,400
 When He ascended the cross, He did not die.

931
00:40:53,400 --> 00:40:54,040
 He resurrected.

932
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:56,960
 After He resurrected, He ascended to heaven.

933
00:40:56,960 --> 00:40:57,760
 Where is He now?

934
00:40:57,760 --> 00:41:02,560
 He is now sitting on the right hand of the Almighty.

935
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:05,040
 I tell you, the author of the book of Hebrews

936
00:41:05,040 --> 00:41:07,680
 loved the 110 chapters of the book of Hebrews.

937
00:41:07,680 --> 00:41:14,120
 He loved it so much that he quoted the first chapter five times.

938
00:41:14,120 --> 00:41:16,440
 We can say that the whole book of Hebrews

939
00:41:16,440 --> 00:41:22,440
 was written based on the 110 chapters of the book of Hebrews.

940
00:41:22,440 --> 00:41:28,320
 This is the first time he quoted the 110 chapters of the book of Hebrews.

941
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:30,080
 He reminds us where Jesus is now.

942
00:41:30,080 --> 00:41:33,760
 He tells us that Jesus is now on the highest heaven.

943
00:41:33,760 --> 00:41:35,080
 He tells us where Jesus is now.

944
00:41:35,080 --> 00:41:38,200
 He is on the right hand of God.

945
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:40,520
 On the highest heaven, on the right hand of God.

946
00:41:40,520 --> 00:41:41,520
 Not only that,

947
00:41:41,520 --> 00:41:43,200
 but He also reminds us of another thing.

948
00:41:43,200 --> 00:41:46,280
 He says, "Look at Jesus.

949
00:41:46,280 --> 00:41:48,160
 He is not standing there.

950
00:41:48,160 --> 00:41:50,520
 He is sitting there."

951
00:41:50,520 --> 00:41:52,520
 What's the difference?

952
00:41:52,520 --> 00:41:54,840
 If He is tired, He can just sit there.

953
00:41:54,840 --> 00:41:56,040
 No.

954
00:41:56,040 --> 00:41:59,000
 He has already achieved His salvation,

955
00:41:59,000 --> 00:42:00,760
 so He can sit there.

956
00:42:00,760 --> 00:42:02,680
 The author of the book of Hebrews tells us,

957
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:07,960
 "You have to pay attention to where Jesus is.

958
00:42:07,960 --> 00:42:12,120
 You have to pay attention to the position of Jesus' body.

959
00:42:12,120 --> 00:42:15,760
 The position of Jesus and the position of His body

960
00:42:15,760 --> 00:42:21,480
 is a great expectation for us Christians."

961
00:42:21,480 --> 00:42:25,600
 What kind of expectation?

962
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:28,000
 In the 10th chapter of the book of Hebrews,

963
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:28,600
 the 11th chapter,

964
00:42:28,600 --> 00:42:30,840
 this is the expectation of us Christians.

965
00:42:30,840 --> 00:42:33,840
 All the priests are standing there every day to serve God.

966
00:42:33,840 --> 00:42:35,400
 Can you see what the priests are doing?

967
00:42:35,400 --> 00:42:35,960
 They are standing there.

968
00:42:35,960 --> 00:42:36,880
 Why?

969
00:42:36,880 --> 00:42:38,920
 No matter how they serve God,

970
00:42:38,920 --> 00:42:41,600
 no matter how they kill the animals,

971
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:43,200
 they can't get rid of their sins.

972
00:42:43,200 --> 00:42:44,800
 They are standing there to serve God.

973
00:42:44,800 --> 00:42:47,040
 And also,

974
00:42:47,040 --> 00:42:48,960
 like the workers in Amazon,

975
00:42:48,960 --> 00:42:50,120
 and also,

976
00:42:50,120 --> 00:42:51,000
 and also,

977
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:52,440
 they can't sit still.

978
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:54,880
 "They are offering the same offering over and over again.

979
00:42:54,880 --> 00:42:58,680
 This offering can never be removed."

980
00:42:58,680 --> 00:42:59,760
 But what about Jesus?

981
00:42:59,760 --> 00:43:06,080
 "But Jesus offered an ever-valuable offering."

982
00:43:06,080 --> 00:43:06,960
 What is He now?

983
00:43:06,960 --> 00:43:08,040
 He is not standing there.

984
00:43:08,040 --> 00:43:09,280
 He is sitting there.

985
00:43:09,280 --> 00:43:13,840
 He is sitting on the right side of God.

986
00:43:13,840 --> 00:43:15,000
 Jesus is sitting there.

987
00:43:15,000 --> 00:43:18,000
 He is telling us that this is the expectation of Christians.

988
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:20,320
 What is the expectation of Christians?

989
00:43:20,320 --> 00:43:21,440
 To be saved from sin,

990
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:22,640
 to be faithful to God,

991
00:43:22,640 --> 00:43:23,880
 to be in harmony with God,

992
00:43:23,880 --> 00:43:25,280
 to be God's offspring,

993
00:43:25,280 --> 00:43:26,720
 to enter heaven,

994
00:43:26,720 --> 00:43:28,000
 and to have eternal life.

995
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:31,200
 These are the expectations of Christians.

996
00:43:31,200 --> 00:43:34,480
 Jesus is now sitting on the right side of God.

997
00:43:34,480 --> 00:43:37,600
 He is giving us these expectations.

998
00:43:37,600 --> 00:43:39,520
 Nothing else is the expectation of Christians.

999
00:43:39,520 --> 00:43:41,360
 The expectation of Christians

1000
00:43:41,360 --> 00:43:46,720
 is to start everything from the highest level.

1001
00:43:46,720 --> 00:43:48,200
 You know that recently,

1002
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:50,360
 because of my wife's illness,

1003
00:43:50,360 --> 00:43:54,960
 I went to a lot of different doctors with her.

1004
00:43:54,960 --> 00:43:58,200
 Yesterday, I went to a doctor's clinic.

1005
00:43:58,200 --> 00:43:59,240
 While I was waiting,

1006
00:43:59,240 --> 00:44:02,280
 I was curious and looked around to see what was going on.

1007
00:44:02,280 --> 00:44:04,480
 This doctor was great.

1008
00:44:04,480 --> 00:44:06,720
 A lot of patients

1009
00:44:06,720 --> 00:44:08,240
 were cured by him.

1010
00:44:08,240 --> 00:44:10,840
 So I gave him a lot of gifts,

1011
00:44:10,840 --> 00:44:12,120
 a lot of souvenirs.

1012
00:44:12,120 --> 00:44:15,040
 So I looked around to see what was written on the gifts.

1013
00:44:15,040 --> 00:44:16,960
 "Miracle of the heart"

1014
00:44:16,960 --> 00:44:18,920
 "Forever in the world"

1015
00:44:18,920 --> 00:44:20,640
 "Long live the Church"

1016
00:44:20,640 --> 00:44:22,960
 These are the gifts.

1017
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:24,120
 But I was thinking,

1018
00:44:24,120 --> 00:44:26,920
 if one day you go to a doctor's clinic,

1019
00:44:26,920 --> 00:44:29,440
 and you see that this doctor has a lot of souvenirs,

1020
00:44:29,440 --> 00:44:31,840
 a lot of people give him gifts,

1021
00:44:31,840 --> 00:44:35,320
 but the words written on the gifts are

1022
00:44:35,320 --> 00:44:37,080
 "Eye-catching"

1023
00:44:37,080 --> 00:44:38,480
 "Turning the world upside down"

1024
00:44:38,480 --> 00:44:40,880
 "Gold-plated"

1025
00:44:40,880 --> 00:44:43,240
 Do you think it's strange?

1026
00:44:43,240 --> 00:44:44,920
 Did I go to the wrong place?

1027
00:44:44,920 --> 00:44:47,360
 Or did the person who gave the gifts

1028
00:44:47,360 --> 00:44:50,720
 misremembered a souvenir?

1029
00:44:50,720 --> 00:44:51,760
 If you look at it again,

1030
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:53,600
 it says "Long-lasting"

1031
00:44:53,600 --> 00:44:55,000
 "God's will"

1032
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:57,080
 "Turning the world upside down"

1033
00:44:57,080 --> 00:45:00,120
 Do you think it's too much?

1034
00:45:00,120 --> 00:45:02,040
 Is this really a doctor?

1035
00:45:02,040 --> 00:45:04,440
 Or is this the Virgin Mary?

1036
00:45:04,440 --> 00:45:06,920
 I want to ask you something.

1037
00:45:06,920 --> 00:45:09,320
 If you have received Jesus' grace,

1038
00:45:09,320 --> 00:45:12,360
 and you have a strong desire for Jesus,

1039
00:45:12,360 --> 00:45:15,200
 and now you want to give Jesus a gift,

1040
00:45:15,200 --> 00:45:16,440
 give Jesus a souvenir,

1041
00:45:16,440 --> 00:45:18,840
 what will you write?

1042
00:45:18,840 --> 00:45:20,040
 Do you understand what I mean?

1043
00:45:20,040 --> 00:45:21,520
 A lot of us misunderstand

1044
00:45:21,520 --> 00:45:24,440
 and don't know who Jesus is.

1045
00:45:24,440 --> 00:45:27,840
 So, we thank Jesus for guarding people's hearts.

1046
00:45:27,840 --> 00:45:29,840
 We thank Jesus for financial wealth.

1047
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:33,600
 We thank Jesus for the end of the world.

1048
00:45:33,600 --> 00:45:35,480
 It's crazy!

1049
00:45:35,480 --> 00:45:37,120
 It's all wrong!

1050
00:45:37,120 --> 00:45:40,320
 Jesus' real gift to us is

1051
00:45:40,320 --> 00:45:43,520
 "to drink, to eat, to sleep, to be obedient, to be pure, to be in harmony with God,

1052
00:45:43,520 --> 00:45:44,800
 to be God's children,

1053
00:45:44,800 --> 00:45:45,960
 to enter God's heaven,

1054
00:45:45,960 --> 00:45:48,800
 and to be God's descendants forever."

1055
00:45:48,800 --> 00:45:52,640
 This is the most precious thing in the Bible.

1056
00:45:52,640 --> 00:45:55,480
 The people written in the Bible

1057
00:45:55,480 --> 00:45:58,960
 have a very miserable life.

1058
00:45:58,960 --> 00:46:00,800
 They are under great pressure.

1059
00:46:00,800 --> 00:46:02,600
 He didn't tell them

1060
00:46:02,600 --> 00:46:06,160
 that the only hope we have is that God can save us

1061
00:46:06,160 --> 00:46:07,720
 from this misery.

1062
00:46:07,720 --> 00:46:10,760
 He pointed to their only hope,

1063
00:46:10,760 --> 00:46:11,960
 their sin, to save their lives.

1064
00:46:11,960 --> 00:46:15,440
 Why can Jesus save our sins?

1065
00:46:15,440 --> 00:46:17,680
 Because he said in chapter 9,

1066
00:46:17,680 --> 00:46:22,200
 "For there is no image of the real church in the Bible,

1067
00:46:22,200 --> 00:46:23,600
 the image of the real church,

1068
00:46:23,600 --> 00:46:24,760
 the church on earth."

1069
00:46:24,760 --> 00:46:25,480
 So, you remember,

1070
00:46:25,480 --> 00:46:27,360
 he kept reminding you where Jesus is.

1071
00:46:27,360 --> 00:46:28,840
 Jesus is in heaven.

1072
00:46:28,840 --> 00:46:29,560
 Jesus is not on earth.

1073
00:46:29,560 --> 00:46:32,120
 If Jesus is buried on earth,

1074
00:46:32,120 --> 00:46:34,120
 if there is no resurrection, if there is no ascension,

1075
00:46:34,120 --> 00:46:35,840
 can Jesus save us?

1076
00:46:35,840 --> 00:46:36,640
 He can't.

1077
00:46:36,640 --> 00:46:37,880
 Why can Jesus save us?

1078
00:46:37,880 --> 00:46:42,720
 Because he is in heaven now.

1079
00:46:42,720 --> 00:46:45,320
 He has entered heaven.

1080
00:46:45,320 --> 00:46:47,640
 He is not a man-made saint,

1081
00:46:47,640 --> 00:46:49,000
 but he has entered heaven,

1082
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:51,120
 appeared before God,

1083
00:46:51,120 --> 00:46:54,600
 and offered himself to the Lord only once

1084
00:46:54,600 --> 00:46:57,720
 to atone for his sins.

1085
00:46:57,720 --> 00:46:59,080
 Jesus is in heaven.

1086
00:46:59,080 --> 00:47:00,000
 This is very important.

1087
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:02,880
 If he offered himself to God on earth, it would be useless.

1088
00:47:02,880 --> 00:47:04,840
 He must be in heaven,

1089
00:47:04,840 --> 00:47:07,240
 on the right side of God in heaven.

1090
00:47:07,240 --> 00:47:09,520
 He offered himself to God.

1091
00:47:09,520 --> 00:47:11,880
 Hebrews chapter 8, verse 1,

1092
00:47:11,880 --> 00:47:14,640
 "For we have such a great master."

1093
00:47:14,640 --> 00:47:17,000
 He is already in heaven.

1094
00:47:17,000 --> 00:47:18,600
 He is not standing, but sitting.

1095
00:47:18,600 --> 00:47:21,960
 "He is sitting on the right side of heaven,

1096
00:47:21,960 --> 00:47:22,840
 in the church."

1097
00:47:22,840 --> 00:47:25,320
 The church is not the church on earth.

1098
00:47:25,320 --> 00:47:31,560
 "For the truth is not the truth, but the truth is the truth of the Lord,

1099
00:47:31,560 --> 00:47:33,800
 and not of man."

1100
00:47:33,800 --> 00:47:34,480
 Who is Jesus?

1101
00:47:34,480 --> 00:47:35,280
 He is in heaven.

1102
00:47:35,280 --> 00:47:36,040
 What is Jesus doing?

1103
00:47:36,040 --> 00:47:36,920
 He is sitting there.

1104
00:47:36,920 --> 00:47:42,680
 He has completed all his salvation.

1105
00:47:42,680 --> 00:47:43,280
 So, let me tell you,

1106
00:47:43,280 --> 00:47:48,640
 the age of our church is less than a century.

1107
00:47:48,640 --> 00:47:50,600
 What I said this week is very reasonable.

1108
00:47:50,600 --> 00:47:51,520
 Because on Thursday,

1109
00:47:51,520 --> 00:47:52,640
 something happened,

1110
00:47:52,640 --> 00:47:53,920
 which is our Ascension Day.

1111
00:47:53,920 --> 00:47:57,360
 But there is no Ascension Day in our church.

1112
00:47:57,360 --> 00:47:58,600
 You have been in church for so long,

1113
00:47:58,600 --> 00:48:02,040
 or the Hong Kong government gives you a holiday.

1114
00:48:02,040 --> 00:48:04,080
 Every time you go, it is Christmas,

1115
00:48:04,080 --> 00:48:04,720
 Good Friday,

1116
00:48:04,720 --> 00:48:05,480
 Lent,

1117
00:48:05,480 --> 00:48:06,120
 and Resurrection Day.

1118
00:48:06,120 --> 00:48:09,000
 Will the government give you an Ascension Day?

1119
00:48:09,000 --> 00:48:11,280
 We should have a request.

1120
00:48:11,280 --> 00:48:13,320
 The government must give me an Ascension Day.

1121
00:48:13,320 --> 00:48:17,640
 Otherwise, our salvation is not complete.

1122
00:48:17,640 --> 00:48:20,560
 The government does not understand our Christian faith.

1123
00:48:20,560 --> 00:48:27,360
 There are four things in our Christian faith, which must be done.

1124
00:48:27,360 --> 00:48:28,880
 We should not let go of Friday,

1125
00:48:28,880 --> 00:48:33,840
 but we should let go of Ascension Day.

1126
00:48:33,840 --> 00:48:35,640
 Jesus came down from heaven.

1127
00:48:35,640 --> 00:48:37,800
 He is the representative of the Holy Spirit.

1128
00:48:37,800 --> 00:48:39,240
 He came to all of us.

1129
00:48:39,240 --> 00:48:40,680
 He cried out to us,

1130
00:48:40,680 --> 00:48:43,760
 "The end of the world is near. You should repent."

1131
00:48:43,760 --> 00:48:44,680
 He did not cry out to us,

1132
00:48:44,680 --> 00:48:47,120
 "Follow me as a human being.

1133
00:48:47,120 --> 00:48:50,320
 Follow my wisdom of life.

1134
00:48:50,320 --> 00:48:52,040
 I will teach you how to be a good person."

1135
00:48:52,040 --> 00:48:52,800
 No, no.

1136
00:48:52,800 --> 00:48:56,800
 He said, "The end of the world is near. You should repent."

1137
00:48:56,800 --> 00:48:58,520
 Then he went up the cross for us,

1138
00:48:58,520 --> 00:48:59,680
 and went out of the tomb for us.

1139
00:48:59,680 --> 00:49:00,400
 He left the world.

1140
00:49:00,400 --> 00:49:02,080
 He ascended.

1141
00:49:02,080 --> 00:49:04,280
 He is the representative of repentance.

1142
00:49:04,280 --> 00:49:05,440
 When he ascended to heaven,

1143
00:49:05,440 --> 00:49:06,520
 he represented us.

1144
00:49:06,520 --> 00:49:08,960
 Why did he pray to God?

1145
00:49:08,960 --> 00:49:11,360
 It is like a country that has been translated.

1146
00:49:11,360 --> 00:49:13,640
 He came to a big country to pray.

1147
00:49:13,640 --> 00:49:15,400
 What do you have to do when you pray?

1148
00:49:15,400 --> 00:49:18,080
 You need a gift.

1149
00:49:18,080 --> 00:49:19,080
 What is Jesus' gift?

1150
00:49:19,080 --> 00:49:19,800
 It is himself.

1151
00:49:19,800 --> 00:49:21,880
 Jesus' gift is his blood.

1152
00:49:21,880 --> 00:49:28,040
 Jesus' gift is his perfect and unsullied baptism.

1153
00:49:28,040 --> 00:49:30,160
 He is not only a Baptist,

1154
00:49:30,160 --> 00:49:33,080
 he is also a Christian.

1155
00:49:33,080 --> 00:49:34,240
 So Jesus rose from the dead.

1156
00:49:34,240 --> 00:49:35,160
 He was crucified.

1157
00:49:35,160 --> 00:49:35,880
 He was resurrected.

1158
00:49:35,880 --> 00:49:37,080
 He ascended to heaven.

1159
00:49:37,080 --> 00:49:40,280
 Jesus' four great missions are inseparable.

1160
00:49:40,280 --> 00:49:42,120
 In fact, there is one more.

1161
00:49:42,120 --> 00:49:44,320
 Are the five great missions better?

1162
00:49:44,320 --> 00:49:46,520
 It is true that the five great missions are inseparable.

1163
00:49:46,520 --> 00:49:48,360
 Jesus has one more mission at the end.

1164
00:49:48,360 --> 00:49:52,160
 He will come back to judge the world.

1165
00:49:52,160 --> 00:49:55,520
 This is what is said in the Bible.

1166
00:49:55,520 --> 00:49:56,240
 He is the King of Kings.

1167
00:49:56,240 --> 00:49:59,120
 The King of Kings will come back to judge the world.

1168
00:49:59,120 --> 00:50:00,880
 Jesus will definitely come back.

1169
00:50:00,880 --> 00:50:01,640
 He was crucified.

1170
00:50:01,640 --> 00:50:02,360
 He was crucified.

1171
00:50:02,360 --> 00:50:03,280
 He ascended to heaven.

1172
00:50:03,280 --> 00:50:03,800
 He was resurrected.

1173
00:50:03,800 --> 00:50:04,840
 He ascended to heaven.

1174
00:50:04,840 --> 00:50:06,720
 He will come back.

1175
00:50:06,720 --> 00:50:09,600
 One day, he will stand up again.

1176
00:50:09,600 --> 00:50:10,920
 He will not sit there anymore.

1177
00:50:10,920 --> 00:50:11,920
 He will come back.

1178
00:50:11,920 --> 00:50:18,520
 He will judge every sinner in this world.

1179
00:50:18,520 --> 00:50:21,160
 Are you ready?

1180
00:50:21,160 --> 00:50:22,800
 Are you ready?

1181
00:50:22,800 --> 00:50:25,440
 Do you know who Jesus is?

1182
00:50:25,440 --> 00:50:30,840
 When Jesus comes to judge you,

1183
00:50:30,840 --> 00:50:32,600
 can you bear it?

1184
00:50:32,600 --> 00:50:33,080
 Let me tell you.

1185
00:50:33,080 --> 00:50:34,040
 There is one person who is not ready.

1186
00:50:34,040 --> 00:50:35,240
 There is one person who is not ready.

1187
00:50:35,240 --> 00:50:37,680
 That person is the priest.

1188
00:50:37,680 --> 00:50:39,200
 So Jesus said to him,

1189
00:50:39,200 --> 00:50:43,240
 "You are not welcome in the kingdom of God."

1190
00:50:43,240 --> 00:50:45,240
 "You are not in the kingdom of God."

1191
00:50:45,240 --> 00:50:45,720
 Why?

1192
00:50:45,720 --> 00:50:48,760
 Because this person is a fool.

1193
00:50:48,760 --> 00:50:49,840
 He asked Jesus,

1194
00:50:49,840 --> 00:50:51,520
 "What is the main point of the Law?"

1195
00:50:51,520 --> 00:50:52,720
 Jesus said to him, "To love God and to love people."

1196
00:50:52,720 --> 00:50:54,560
 He said, "OK, OK, to love God and to love people."

1197
00:50:54,560 --> 00:50:57,920
 "I will no longer be involved in these useless things."

1198
00:50:57,920 --> 00:50:59,400
 "I will go out and be a good person."

1199
00:50:59,400 --> 00:51:01,960
 "I want to love God. I want to love people."

1200
00:51:01,960 --> 00:51:04,440
 "I want to serve my community."

1201
00:51:04,440 --> 00:51:05,520
 He thought he was very wise.

1202
00:51:05,520 --> 00:51:07,080
 So Jesus answered him,

1203
00:51:07,080 --> 00:51:08,320
 "You are not welcome in the kingdom of God."

1204
00:51:08,320 --> 00:51:09,440
 Jesus said to him,

1205
00:51:09,440 --> 00:51:10,480
 "You don't know me at all."

1206
00:51:10,480 --> 00:51:12,560
 "You don't know that you are not in the kingdom of God."

1207
00:51:12,560 --> 00:51:14,080
 "You cannot enter the kingdom of God."

1208
00:51:14,080 --> 00:51:14,360
 Why?

1209
00:51:14,360 --> 00:51:16,040
 Because for this person,

1210
00:51:16,040 --> 00:51:19,160
 Jesus was only a good teacher.

1211
00:51:19,160 --> 00:51:22,000
 Jesus was not a Savior.

1212
00:51:22,000 --> 00:51:24,640
 So at the end, I would like to ask you.

1213
00:51:24,640 --> 00:51:26,000
 I would like to ask you.

1214
00:51:26,000 --> 00:51:28,640
 I would like to ask you a very important question

1215
00:51:28,640 --> 00:51:31,760
 through our last episode.

1216
00:51:31,760 --> 00:51:34,240
 Not only do you need to know what the answer is,

1217
00:51:34,240 --> 00:51:38,400
 but you also need to believe wholeheartedly.

1218
00:51:38,400 --> 00:51:40,960
 What is the core of Christianity?

1219
00:51:40,960 --> 00:51:43,680
 If today someone examines you,

1220
00:51:43,680 --> 00:51:45,840
 what is the core of Christianity?

1221
00:51:45,840 --> 00:51:46,880
 The core of Christianity?

1222
00:51:46,880 --> 00:51:48,320
 You may have been in the church for a long time.

1223
00:51:48,320 --> 00:51:49,360
 You may have been in the synagogue for a long time.

1224
00:51:49,360 --> 00:51:50,400
 Or you may have been in another church for a long time.

1225
00:51:50,400 --> 00:51:51,120
 I would like to ask you.

1226
00:51:51,120 --> 00:51:53,320
 What is the core of Christianity?

1227
00:51:53,320 --> 00:51:54,960
 Choose one.

1228
00:51:54,960 --> 00:51:57,520
 Is it A or 1?

1229
00:51:57,520 --> 00:52:00,480
 "Follow Christ and love God and love people."

1230
00:52:00,480 --> 00:52:01,520
 Very attractive.

1231
00:52:01,520 --> 00:52:03,160
 Or is it E or B?

1232
00:52:03,160 --> 00:52:03,920
 Have you heard of it?

1233
00:52:03,920 --> 00:52:05,200
 It is a golden rule.

1234
00:52:05,200 --> 00:52:06,720
 It is a golden rule.

1235
00:52:06,720 --> 00:52:10,400
 "People treat you, and you treat people."

1236
00:52:10,400 --> 00:52:10,960
 Do you believe it?

1237
00:52:10,960 --> 00:52:13,520
 At that time, some laymen answered this question.

1238
00:52:13,520 --> 00:52:15,760
 They said, "What is the core of the whole law?"

1239
00:52:15,760 --> 00:52:18,240
 "People treat you, and you treat people."

1240
00:52:18,240 --> 00:52:20,480
 Or is it C or B?

1241
00:52:20,480 --> 00:52:22,640
 "Leadership is more blessed."

1242
00:52:22,640 --> 00:52:27,040
 These are all the words you learned when you were young.

1243
00:52:27,040 --> 00:52:30,800
 What is the core of Christianity?

1244
00:52:30,800 --> 00:52:32,080
 1, 2, or 3?

1245
00:52:32,080 --> 00:52:33,920
 You said, "Pastor Lam, it is difficult to choose."

1246
00:52:33,920 --> 00:52:35,120
 "Everyone wants to choose."

1247
00:52:35,120 --> 00:52:35,920
 "Everyone is like this."

1248
00:52:35,920 --> 00:52:37,280
 "It doesn't matter. I will give you the 4th one."

1249
00:52:37,280 --> 00:52:39,920
 "All of the above."

1250
00:52:39,920 --> 00:52:42,000
 Is it right?

1251
00:52:42,000 --> 00:52:42,960
 It must be right.

1252
00:52:42,960 --> 00:52:43,760
 "All of the above."

1253
00:52:43,760 --> 00:52:45,520
 The answer is not "All of the above."

1254
00:52:45,520 --> 00:52:48,880
 It is "None of the above."

1255
00:52:48,880 --> 00:52:49,840
 It is completely wrong.

1256
00:52:49,840 --> 00:52:52,160
 If you choose one of them, or choose the 4th one,

1257
00:52:52,160 --> 00:52:54,960
 you are completely wrong.

1258
00:52:54,960 --> 00:52:55,520
 Why?

1259
00:52:55,520 --> 00:52:58,000
 Because that is not the core of our faith.

1260
00:52:58,000 --> 00:52:59,760
 The core of our faith is

1261
00:52:59,760 --> 00:53:01,440
 how you view Christ.

1262
00:53:01,440 --> 00:53:02,640
 Who is Christ?

1263
00:53:02,640 --> 00:53:05,040
 This is the core of our faith.

1264
00:53:05,040 --> 00:53:07,600
 Two weeks ago,

1265
00:53:07,600 --> 00:53:12,000
 when I was preparing for my English class,

1266
00:53:12,000 --> 00:53:13,120
 I thought of a book.

1267
00:53:13,120 --> 00:53:18,160
 It is called "In His Steps."

1268
00:53:18,160 --> 00:53:19,120
 This book is very old.

1269
00:53:19,120 --> 00:53:21,680
 It was written in 1896.

1270
00:53:21,680 --> 00:53:24,800
 But there are new versions of it.

1271
00:53:24,800 --> 00:53:29,680
 Recently, it is still airing on TV.

1272
00:53:29,680 --> 00:53:31,200
 "In His Steps" is about

1273
00:53:31,200 --> 00:53:33,040
 a group of people

1274
00:53:33,040 --> 00:53:34,640
 who have a Sunday evening

1275
00:53:34,640 --> 00:53:36,320
 in a small church town.

1276
00:53:36,320 --> 00:53:38,880
 Suddenly, they feel moved.

1277
00:53:38,880 --> 00:53:41,600
 "Why don't we start from this week?"

1278
00:53:41,600 --> 00:53:42,960
 "Let us see our disciples."

1279
00:53:42,960 --> 00:53:45,520
 "Let us serve them like Jesus."

1280
00:53:45,520 --> 00:53:48,400
 "Let us see how God will glorify Himself."

1281
00:53:48,400 --> 00:53:50,080
 So, the story begins.

1282
00:53:50,080 --> 00:53:51,040
 This is a false story.

1283
00:53:51,040 --> 00:53:52,000
 I don't mean it to be false.

1284
00:53:52,000 --> 00:53:52,880
 I mean it is fictional.

1285
00:53:52,880 --> 00:53:55,200
 It is created by God Himself.

1286
00:53:55,200 --> 00:53:56,080
 In this story,

1287
00:53:56,080 --> 00:54:00,560
 many people start to influence other people's lives.

1288
00:54:00,560 --> 00:54:01,840
 It is like Jesus.

1289
00:54:01,840 --> 00:54:04,160
 When Jesus saw this scripture,

1290
00:54:04,160 --> 00:54:05,200
 He did what He had to do.

1291
00:54:05,200 --> 00:54:08,480
 So, the whole town is completely different.

1292
00:54:08,480 --> 00:54:09,760
 It is completely different after a week.

1293
00:54:09,760 --> 00:54:16,560
 This story becomes the Christian faith of many people.

1294
00:54:16,560 --> 00:54:20,000
 Have you ever heard of it?

1295
00:54:20,000 --> 00:54:21,600
 "What will Jesus do?"

1296
00:54:21,600 --> 00:54:23,120
 What will Jesus do?

1297
00:54:23,120 --> 00:54:24,400
 One of the most important principles.

1298
00:54:24,400 --> 00:54:25,440
 When you see a person,

1299
00:54:25,440 --> 00:54:28,400
 whether it is on the street or at home,

1300
00:54:28,400 --> 00:54:30,560
 you see a person who does not like his brother,

1301
00:54:30,560 --> 00:54:31,440
 but his brother likes him,

1302
00:54:31,440 --> 00:54:33,360
 and when his brother hurts his brother,

1303
00:54:33,360 --> 00:54:35,200
 you say, "What will Jesus do?"

1304
00:54:35,200 --> 00:54:35,600
 Right?

1305
00:54:35,600 --> 00:54:38,320
 You think this is a very good principle.

1306
00:54:38,320 --> 00:54:40,240
 Think about how Jesus will treat your brother.

1307
00:54:40,240 --> 00:54:42,080
 How will Jesus treat your brother?

1308
00:54:42,080 --> 00:54:43,760
 This becomes our principle.

1309
00:54:43,760 --> 00:54:44,960
 But have you noticed one thing?

1310
00:54:44,960 --> 00:54:46,320
 "What will Jesus do?"

1311
00:54:46,320 --> 00:54:50,400
 It covers the cross of Jesus.

1312
00:54:50,400 --> 00:54:51,200
 It is gone.

1313
00:54:51,200 --> 00:54:55,200
 We can only see Jesus as a teacher.

1314
00:54:55,200 --> 00:54:56,720
 Jesus as a teacher.

1315
00:54:56,720 --> 00:54:58,720
 But we can't see the tomb of Jesus.

1316
00:54:58,720 --> 00:55:00,880
 We can't see his cross.

1317
00:55:00,880 --> 00:55:02,400
 We can't see his sanctification.

1318
00:55:02,400 --> 00:55:04,800
 We can't see his crucifixion.

1319
00:55:04,800 --> 00:55:09,120
 We can't see "He will come again."

1320
00:55:09,120 --> 00:55:11,920
 What is the core of Christian faith?

1321
00:55:11,920 --> 00:55:13,840
 It is the dead king,

1322
00:55:13,840 --> 00:55:16,720
 the ever-living teacher.

1323
00:55:16,720 --> 00:55:19,920
 Or the other Jesus

1324
00:55:19,920 --> 00:55:21,200
 who has shown himself,

1325
00:55:21,200 --> 00:55:22,320
 who has shown himself,

1326
00:55:22,320 --> 00:55:24,960
 is the risen, dead, resurrected, sanctified,

1327
00:55:24,960 --> 00:55:27,520
 who will come again to judge the world.

1328
00:55:27,520 --> 00:55:32,000
 This is the echo we want to convey.

1329
00:55:32,000 --> 00:55:32,880
 Where is Jesus today?

1330
00:55:32,880 --> 00:55:35,360
 He is sitting on the right hand of God.

1331
00:55:35,360 --> 00:55:37,360
 He has taken over the world.

1332
00:55:37,360 --> 00:55:39,520
 He is sitting here.

1333
00:55:39,520 --> 00:55:41,520
 He has atoned for us.

1334
00:55:41,520 --> 00:55:45,920
 There is no other Savior in this world.

1335
00:55:45,920 --> 00:55:46,560
 I want to ask you.

1336
00:55:46,560 --> 00:55:51,040
 I'm not asking you if you have the scent of Christ.

1337
00:55:51,040 --> 00:55:52,000
 Sometimes we like to ask,

1338
00:55:52,000 --> 00:55:52,800
 the Christian Church likes to ask,

1339
00:55:52,800 --> 00:55:54,240
 "Do you have the scent of Christ?"

1340
00:55:54,240 --> 00:55:56,960
 What does that mean?

1341
00:55:56,960 --> 00:55:58,080
 Do you have the scent of Christ?

1342
00:55:58,080 --> 00:55:59,280
 Do you have the scent of Christ?

1343
00:55:59,280 --> 00:56:00,160
 This is an important question,

1344
00:56:00,160 --> 00:56:03,200
 but it is a secondary question.

1345
00:56:03,200 --> 00:56:05,680
 Do you believe in Jesus?

1346
00:56:05,680 --> 00:56:07,760
 Do you know that he is the only Savior

1347
00:56:07,760 --> 00:56:10,080
 who has risen, died, resurrected,

1348
00:56:10,080 --> 00:56:16,320
 and sat on the right hand of God for us?

1349
00:56:16,320 --> 00:56:17,120
 At the end of the sermon,

1350
00:56:17,120 --> 00:56:19,840
 I want to give you two chapters of the Bible,

1351
00:56:19,840 --> 00:56:21,360
 the description of Hebrews.

1352
00:56:21,360 --> 00:56:22,000
 Hebrews said,

1353
00:56:22,000 --> 00:56:23,680
 "Do you know where Jesus is?

1354
00:56:23,680 --> 00:56:25,360
 He is sitting on the right hand of God."

1355
00:56:25,360 --> 00:56:28,080
 This is the first chapter of Hebrews chapter 5,

1356
00:56:28,080 --> 00:56:32,960
 verse 110.

1357
00:56:32,960 --> 00:56:33,840
 Hebrews said,

1358
00:56:33,840 --> 00:56:38,160
 "Therefore, since we have so many witnesses

1359
00:56:38,160 --> 00:56:39,840
 who are like clouds surrounding us,

1360
00:56:39,840 --> 00:56:43,040
 we should cast down all kinds of heavy burdens,

1361
00:56:43,040 --> 00:56:46,880
 and do what is most necessary,

1362
00:56:46,880 --> 00:56:49,760
 and a firm heart

1363
00:56:49,760 --> 00:56:53,200
 shall not be put in our way."

1364
00:56:53,200 --> 00:56:53,920
 Brothers and sisters,

1365
00:56:53,920 --> 00:56:54,480
 dear friends,

1366
00:56:54,480 --> 00:56:55,680
 I want to ask you,

1367
00:56:55,680 --> 00:56:58,000
 do you have any burdens?

1368
00:56:58,000 --> 00:57:01,280
 Do you have any sins?

1369
00:57:01,280 --> 00:57:03,360
 Do you know the background of Hebrews?

1370
00:57:03,360 --> 00:57:04,880
 Why does Hebrews write this book?

1371
00:57:04,880 --> 00:57:06,240
 Why does he write 13 chapters?

1372
00:57:06,240 --> 00:57:07,440
 Because there are many Catholics

1373
00:57:07,440 --> 00:57:09,840
 who are leaving the Church in Rome.

1374
00:57:09,840 --> 00:57:11,360
 Why are they leaving the Church?

1375
00:57:11,360 --> 00:57:12,560
 It is because of the power of the Holy Spirit,

1376
00:57:12,560 --> 00:57:13,360
 because of the power of the world,

1377
00:57:13,360 --> 00:57:14,720
 because of the hardship of life,

1378
00:57:14,720 --> 00:57:16,240
 because of the pressure of faith.

1379
00:57:16,240 --> 00:57:17,600
 We do not have the pressure of faith yet,

1380
00:57:17,600 --> 00:57:20,080
 but we seem to have it very soon.

1381
00:57:20,080 --> 00:57:22,080
 But we have both in front of us.

1382
00:57:22,080 --> 00:57:23,360
 We have the power of the world,

1383
00:57:23,360 --> 00:57:24,880
 and we have the hardship of life.

1384
00:57:24,880 --> 00:57:26,880
 Many people say,

1385
00:57:26,880 --> 00:57:28,080
 "Jesus is like this.

1386
00:57:28,080 --> 00:57:31,440
 He does not expect much from me."

1387
00:57:31,440 --> 00:57:32,960
 So they leave the Church.

1388
00:57:32,960 --> 00:57:36,560
 Hebrews writes this book to tell you,

1389
00:57:36,560 --> 00:57:37,600
 "Think no more.

1390
00:57:37,600 --> 00:57:38,240
 You are gone.

1391
00:57:38,240 --> 00:57:38,880
 You are gone.

1392
00:57:38,880 --> 00:57:41,360
 Because otherwise there is no salvation,

1393
00:57:41,360 --> 00:57:45,520
 there is no other Jesus in heaven."

1394
00:57:45,520 --> 00:57:48,560
 How do you face your sin?

1395
00:57:48,560 --> 00:57:50,720
 When God comes back to judge you,

1396
00:57:50,720 --> 00:57:54,640
 how can you enter His kingdom?

1397
00:57:54,640 --> 00:57:55,600
 Never leave.

1398
00:57:55,600 --> 00:58:00,000
 So He encourages them to endure to the end,

1399
00:58:00,000 --> 00:58:03,120
 and to cast aside the confusion of this world,

1400
00:58:03,120 --> 00:58:06,320
 the sins that haunt them.

1401
00:58:06,320 --> 00:58:07,200
 The last verse says,

1402
00:58:07,200 --> 00:58:08,640
 "Look up to our faith,

1403
00:58:08,640 --> 00:58:10,880
 and be like the Lord Jesus."

1404
00:58:10,880 --> 00:58:11,920
 Where is He?

1405
00:58:11,920 --> 00:58:14,640
 "He wears the joy of being in front of you,

1406
00:58:14,640 --> 00:58:16,320
 the lightness, the glory,

1407
00:58:16,320 --> 00:58:17,840
 and the endurance of the cross."

1408
00:58:17,840 --> 00:58:19,360
 Where is He in the cross?

1409
00:58:19,360 --> 00:58:25,440
 "And now He sits on the right hand of the Lord."

1410
00:58:25,440 --> 00:58:26,960
 You need to know Jesus.

1411
00:58:26,960 --> 00:58:29,840
 What did He do in all that He did?

1412
00:58:29,840 --> 00:58:31,040
 He died for us.

1413
00:58:31,040 --> 00:58:32,400
 He rose from the dead for us.

1414
00:58:32,400 --> 00:58:33,440
 He resurrected for us.

1415
00:58:33,440 --> 00:58:35,360
 Where is He now?

1416
00:58:35,360 --> 00:58:36,800
 He is the Savior.

1417
00:58:36,800 --> 00:58:40,960
 There is no salvation without Him.

1418
00:58:40,960 --> 00:58:44,400
 Do you believe that?

1419
00:58:44,400 --> 00:58:45,920
 Look up to Him.

1420
00:58:45,920 --> 00:58:47,760
 Follow Him.

1421
00:58:47,760 --> 00:58:49,520
 Follow the way of Heaven.

1422
00:58:49,520 --> 00:58:51,360
 This is what God has called us to do.

1423
00:58:51,360 --> 00:58:53,680
 May we listen to His call,

1424
00:58:53,680 --> 00:58:54,640
 and respond to His call.

1425
00:58:54,640 --> 00:58:58,000
 This is our prayer.

1426
00:58:58,000 --> 00:58:58,480
 Our Heavenly Father,

1427
00:58:58,480 --> 00:59:01,680
 we truly thank you.

1428
00:59:01,680 --> 00:59:02,320
 Because in the Last Supper,

1429
00:59:02,320 --> 00:59:07,360
 we not only remember David's son,

1430
00:59:07,360 --> 00:59:08,080
 or his descendant.

1431
00:59:08,080 --> 00:59:10,640
 He was also the son of God.

1432
00:59:10,640 --> 00:59:11,440
 But we thank you

1433
00:59:11,440 --> 00:59:16,880
 not because of these questions.

1434
00:59:16,880 --> 00:59:17,680
 Who is Jesus?

1435
00:59:17,680 --> 00:59:20,080
 Yes, I know.

1436
00:59:20,080 --> 00:59:27,280
 The whole gospel is about His resurrection,

1437
00:59:27,280 --> 00:59:32,880
 His death, resurrection, and resurrection.

1438
00:59:32,880 --> 00:59:40,640
 We are in a very vague world.

1439
00:59:40,640 --> 00:59:43,680
 We do not know

1440
00:59:43,680 --> 00:59:47,440
 what is the true faith of Christ.

1441
00:59:47,440 --> 00:59:50,800
 There is no difference between us and the world.

1442
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:51,920
 So when we come to church,

1443
00:59:51,920 --> 00:59:55,760
 we are worried about the current pandemic,

1444
00:59:55,760 --> 00:59:57,280
 the difficulties in life,

1445
00:59:57,280 --> 00:59:59,600
 and the fear of the future.

1446
00:59:59,600 --> 01:00:02,160
 So we look forward to

1447
01:00:02,160 --> 01:00:03,840
 being able to talk about these things in church.

1448
01:00:03,840 --> 01:00:04,720
 On the contrary,

1449
01:00:04,720 --> 01:00:06,080
 when we look at the early church,

1450
01:00:06,080 --> 01:00:10,480
 they point us to another world,

1451
01:00:10,480 --> 01:00:13,920
 where we can see Jesus Christ, who is victorious for us,

1452
01:00:13,920 --> 01:00:18,640
 sitting on the right hand of God's power.

1453
01:00:18,640 --> 01:00:21,520
 He is the only Savior.

1454
01:00:21,520 --> 01:00:23,120
 So we have to endure,

1455
01:00:23,120 --> 01:00:26,160
 we have to persist,

1456
01:00:26,160 --> 01:00:27,200
 in this world,

1457
01:00:27,200 --> 01:00:28,560
 in this short life,

1458
01:00:28,560 --> 01:00:29,520
 to be a witness for you,

1459
01:00:29,520 --> 01:00:30,560
 to ask you to help us,

1460
01:00:30,560 --> 01:00:33,920
 to become a church like this,

1461
01:00:33,920 --> 01:00:37,520
 to follow Jesus,

1462
01:00:37,520 --> 01:00:41,520
 to be a witness for His light.

1463
01:00:41,520 --> 01:00:42,240
 We pray in this way,

1464
01:00:42,240 --> 01:00:43,600
 in the name of Jesus Christ.

1465
01:00:43,600 --> 01:00:44,100
安保

